		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Don't use DIP sockets. Use DIP-to-something-else adapters, where the something-else is a smaller form factor for a 5.0 V flash chip. Then build a hinged access door in the cart.
<br />
<br />Or are the smaller form factors available exclusively in 3.3 V?

		

		</td>
